==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nominalist
<hw>Nom"i*nal*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Metaph.)</fld> <def>One of a
sect of philosophers in the Middle Ages, who adopted the opinion of
<persfn>Roscelin</persfn>, that general conceptions, or universals,
exist in name only.</def> <rj><au>Reid.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

